indicator.description:
i. Number of countries that have formally endorsed the GSF
ii. Existence of an agreement with a suitable host institution to absorb the GSF; 
iii. Number of agreements with beneficiary organizations and other partners; 
iv. Perception of the key national decision makers and other civil society stakeholders of the importance of the GSF to achievement of national and regional conservation priorities; 
v. Number of GSF products that addresses the economic, cultural and political rights of gender groups.
vi. The percentage of regional government cost sharing as a percentage of total funds committed; 
vii. Percentage of GSF funds generated from payment from eco-system services and other mechanisms;
viii. Common agreement on mechanism for the distribution of financial resources.
ix. Media coverage (newspapers, scientific articles and speeches) of GSF at the eco-regional level; 
x. Number of hits to GSF website disaggregated by GS-6 country; 
xi. Number of public and community institutions (projects) regionally that are more effective after accessing capacity building services; 
xii. Number of GS-6 countries using monitoring data collected by GSF for planning and decision making;
xiii. Number of GS-6 countries that are able to prepare quality reports to MEAs using local expertise and GSF generated data.

